            <h3>La Rinascente</h3>
            <p>In particular there are a couple of famous shopping areas in the city, including Milan’s high-end La Rinascente department store, hosting a variety of products in addition to clothing and accessories. La Rinascente is located across from the Milan Cathedral.</p>
            <h3>Via Montenapoleone</h3>
            <p>A few blocks northeast of Piazza del Duomo is Milan’s most famous shopping street, <strong>Via Montenapoleone</strong>, the center of Milan’s main fashion district. Via Montenapoleone is lined with upscale boutiques and stores, and is known as Europe’s most expensive street. Many exclusive stores also exist along this street.</p>
            <h3>Armani/Silos</h3>
            <p>Southwest of Central Milan is a large upscale fashion museum, the Armani/Silos, dedicated to the fashion history of Giorgio Armani brands. The fashion exhibits at this museum are also presented in a very aesthetic manner.</p>
