        <h2 class="left-heading destination-section-heading">Da Vinci's Last Supper</h2>
        <p>Among Milan’s top attractions is the <strong>Chiesa di Santa Maria delle Grazie</strong> (Church of Holy Mary of Grace), a UNESCO world heritage site known for its famous mural of The Last Supper by Leonardo da Vinci. The exterior of this 15th century church / Dominican convent is very beautiful as well, displaying Gothic and Renaissance architectural styles.</p>
        <p>Be sure to book your tour to visit Santa Maria delle Grazie in advance, since it draws an enormous amount of tourists wishing to see da Vinci’s massive mural of The Last Supper. The church is located on the western side of Central Milan, near the Sfrozesco Castle.</p>
    </section>



